98static u64
99nouveau_pci_name(struct pci_dev *pdev)
100{
101 u64 name = (u64)pci_domain_nr(pdev->bus) << 32;
102 name |= pdev->bus->number << 16;
103 name |= PCI_SLOT(pdev->devfn) << 8;
104 return name | PCI_FUNC(pdev->devfn);
105}
106
107static u64
108nouveau_platform_name(struct platform_device *platformdev)
109{
110 return platformdev->id;
111}
112
113static u64
114nouveau_name(struct drm_device *dev)
115{
116 if (dev->pdev)
117 return nouveau_pci_name(dev->pdev);
118 else
119 return nouveau_platform_name(dev->platformdev);
120}
121
122static int
123nouveau_cli_create(struct drm_device *dev, const char *sname,
124 int size, void **pcli)
125{
126 struct nouveau_cli *cli = *pcli = kzalloc(size, GFP_KERNEL);
127 int ret;
128 if (cli) {
129 snprintf(cli->name, sizeof(cli->name), "%s", sname);
130 cli->dev = dev;
131
132 ret = nvif_client_init(NULL, cli->name, nouveau_name(dev),
133 nouveau_config, nouveau_debug,
134 &cli->base);
135 if (ret == 0) {
136#ifdef __NetBSD__
137 linux_mutex_init(&cli->mutex);
138#else
139 mutex_init(&cli->mutex);
140#endif
141 usif_client_init(cli);
142 }
143 return ret;
144 }
145 return -ENOMEM;
146}
147
148static void
149nouveau_cli_destroy(struct nouveau_cli *cli)
150{
151 nvkm_vm_ref(NULL, &nvxx_client(&cli->base)->vm, NULL);
152 nvif_client_fini(&cli->base);
153 usif_client_fini(cli);
154#ifdef __NetBSD__
155 linux_mutex_destroy(&cli->mutex);
156#else
157 mutex_destroy(&cli->mutex);
158#endif
159 kfree(cli);
160}

162static void
163nouveau_accel_fini(struct nouveau_drm *drm)
164{
165 nouveau_channel_idle(drm->channel);
166 nvif_object_fini(&drm->ntfy);
167 nvkm_gpuobj_del(&drm->notify);
168 nvif_notify_fini(&drm->flip);
169 nvif_object_fini(&drm->nvsw);
170 nouveau_channel_del(&drm->channel);
171
172 nouveau_channel_idle(drm->cechan);
173 nvif_object_fini(&drm->ttm.copy);
174 nouveau_channel_del(&drm->cechan);
175
176 if (drm->fence)
177 nouveau_fence(drm)->dtor(drm);
178}
179
180static void
181nouveau_accel_init(struct nouveau_drm *drm)
182{
183 struct nvif_device *device = &drm->device;
184 struct nvif_sclass *sclass;
185 u32 arg0, arg1;
186 int ret, i, n;
187
188 if (nouveau_noaccel)
189 return;
190
191 /* initialise synchronisation routines */
192 /*XXX: this is crap, but the fence/channel stuff is a little
193 * backwards in some places. this will be fixed.
194 */
195 ret = n = nvif_object_sclass_get(&device->object, &sclass);
196 if (ret < 0)
197 return;
198
199 for (ret = -ENOSYS, i = 0; i < n; i++) {
200 switch (sclass[i].oclass) {
201 case NV03_CHANNEL_DMA:
202 ret = nv04_fence_create(drm);
203 break;
204 case NV10_CHANNEL_DMA:
205 ret = nv10_fence_create(drm);
206 break;
207 case NV17_CHANNEL_DMA:
208 case NV40_CHANNEL_DMA:
209 ret = nv17_fence_create(drm);
210 break;
211 case NV50_CHANNEL_GPFIFO:
212 ret = nv50_fence_create(drm);
213 break;
214 case G82_CHANNEL_GPFIFO:
215 ret = nv84_fence_create(drm);
216 break;
217 case FERMI_CHANNEL_GPFIFO:
218 case KEPLER_CHANNEL_GPFIFO_A:
219 case MAXWELL_CHANNEL_GPFIFO_A:
220 ret = nvc0_fence_create(drm);
221 break;
222 default:
223 break;
224 }
225 }
226
227 nvif_object_sclass_put(&sclass);
228 if (ret) {
229 NV_ERROR(drm, "failed to initialise sync subsystem, %d\n", ret);
230 nouveau_accel_fini(drm);
231 return;
232 }
233
234 if (device->info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_KEPLER) {
235 ret = nouveau_channel_new(drm, &drm->device,
236 KEPLER_CHANNEL_GPFIFO_A_V0_ENGINE_CE0|
237 KEPLER_CHANNEL_GPFIFO_A_V0_ENGINE_CE1,
238 0, &drm->cechan);
239 if (ret)
240 NV_ERROR(drm, "failed to create ce channel, %d\n", ret);
241
242 arg0 = KEPLER_CHANNEL_GPFIFO_A_V0_ENGINE_GR;
243 arg1 = 1;
244 } else
245 if (device->info.chipset >= 0xa3 &&
246 device->info.chipset != 0xaa &&
247 device->info.chipset != 0xac) {
248 ret = nouveau_channel_new(drm, &drm->device,
249 NvDmaFB, NvDmaTT, &drm->cechan);
250 if (ret)
251 NV_ERROR(drm, "failed to create ce channel, %d\n", ret);
252
253 arg0 = NvDmaFB;
254 arg1 = NvDmaTT;
255 } else {
256 arg0 = NvDmaFB;
257 arg1 = NvDmaTT;
258 }
259
260 ret = nouveau_channel_new(drm, &drm->device, arg0, arg1, &drm->channel);
261 if (ret) {
262 NV_ERROR(drm, "failed to create kernel channel, %d\n", ret);
263 nouveau_accel_fini(drm);
264 return;
265 }
266
267 ret = nvif_object_init(&drm->channel->user, NVDRM_NVSW,
268 nouveau_abi16_swclass(drm), NULL, 0, &drm->nvsw);
269 if (ret == 0) {
270 ret = RING_SPACE(drm->channel, 2);
271 if (ret == 0) {
272 if (device->info.family < NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_FERMI) {
273 BEGIN_NV04(drm->channel, NvSubSw, 0, 1);
274 OUT_RING (drm->channel, NVDRM_NVSW);
275 } else
276 if (device->info.family < NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_KEPLER) {
277 BEGIN_NVC0(drm->channel, FermiSw, 0, 1);
278 OUT_RING (drm->channel, 0x001f0000);
279 }
280 }
281
282 ret = nvif_notify_init(&drm->nvsw, nouveau_flip_complete,
283 false, NVSW_NTFY_UEVENT, NULL, 0, 0,
284 &drm->flip);
285 if (ret == 0)
286 ret = nvif_notify_get(&drm->flip);
287 if (ret) {
288 nouveau_accel_fini(drm);
289 return;
290 }
291 }
292
293 if (ret) {
294 NV_ERROR(drm, "failed to allocate software object, %d\n", ret);
295 nouveau_accel_fini(drm);
296 return;
297 }
298
299 if (device->info.family < NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_FERMI) {
300 ret = nvkm_gpuobj_new(nvxx_device(&drm->device), 32, 0, false,
301 NULL, &drm->notify);
302 if (ret) {
303 NV_ERROR(drm, "failed to allocate notifier, %d\n", ret);
304 nouveau_accel_fini(drm);
305 return;
306 }
307
308 ret = nvif_object_init(&drm->channel->user, NvNotify0,
309 NV_DMA_IN_MEMORY,
310 &(struct nv_dma_v0) {
311 .target = NV_DMA_V0_TARGET_VRAM,
312 .access = NV_DMA_V0_ACCESS_RDWR,
313 .start = drm->notify->addr,
314 .limit = drm->notify->addr + 31
315 }, sizeof(struct nv_dma_v0),
316 &drm->ntfy);
317 if (ret) {
318 nouveau_accel_fini(drm);
319 return;
320 }
321 }
322
323
324 nouveau_bo_move_init(drm);
325}

327#ifndef __NetBSD__
328static int nouveau_drm_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev,
329 const struct pci_device_id *pent)
330{
331 struct nvkm_device *device;
332 struct apertures_struct *aper;
333 bool boot = false;
334 int ret;
335
336 /* We need to check that the chipset is supported before booting
337 * fbdev off the hardware, as there's no way to put it back.
338 */
339 ret = nvkm_device_pci_new(pdev, NULL, "error", true, false, 0, &device);
340 if (ret)
341 return ret;
342
343 nvkm_device_del(&device);
344
345 /* Remove conflicting drivers (vesafb, efifb etc). */
346 aper = alloc_apertures(3);
347 if (!aper)
348 return -ENOMEM;
349
350 aper->ranges[0].base = pci_resource_start(pdev, 1);
351 aper->ranges[0].size = pci_resource_len(pdev, 1);
352 aper->count = 1;
353
354 if (pci_resource_len(pdev, 2)) {
355 aper->ranges[aper->count].base = pci_resource_start(pdev, 2);
356 aper->ranges[aper->count].size = pci_resource_len(pdev, 2);
357 aper->count++;
358 }
359
360 if (pci_resource_len(pdev, 3)) {
361 aper->ranges[aper->count].base = pci_resource_start(pdev, 3);
362 aper->ranges[aper->count].size = pci_resource_len(pdev, 3);
363 aper->count++;
364 }
365
366#ifdef CONFIG_X86
367 boot = pdev->resource[PCI_ROM_RESOURCE].flags & IORESOURCE_ROM_SHADOW;
368#endif
369 if (nouveau_modeset != 2)
370 remove_conflicting_framebuffers(aper, "nouveaufb", boot);
371 kfree(aper);
372
373 ret = nvkm_device_pci_new(pdev, nouveau_config, nouveau_debug,
374 true, true, ~0ULL, &device);
375 if (ret)
376 return ret;
377
378 pci_set_master(pdev);
379
380 ret = drm_get_pci_dev(pdev, pent, &driver_pci);
381 if (ret) {
382 nvkm_device_del(&device);
383 return ret;
384 }
385
386 return 0;
387}
388#endif

390#define PCI_CLASS_MULTIMEDIA_HD_AUDIO 0x0403
391
392static void
393nouveau_get_hdmi_dev(struct nouveau_drm *drm)
394{
395#ifndef __NetBSD__ /* XXX nouveau hdmi */
396 struct pci_dev *pdev = drm->dev->pdev;
397
398 if (!pdev) {
399 DRM_INFO("not a PCI device; no HDMI\n");
400 drm->hdmi_device = NULL;
401 return;
402 }
403
404 /* subfunction one is a hdmi audio device? */
405 drm->hdmi_device = pci_get_bus_and_slot((unsigned int)pdev->bus->number,
406 PCI_DEVFN(PCI_SLOT(pdev->devfn), 1));
407
408 if (!drm->hdmi_device) {
409 NV_DEBUG(drm, "hdmi device not found %d %d %d\n", pdev->bus->number, PCI_SLOT(pdev->devfn), 1);
410 return;
411 }
412
413 if ((drm->hdmi_device->class >> 8) != PCI_CLASS_MULTIMEDIA_HD_AUDIO) {
414 NV_DEBUG(drm, "possible hdmi device not audio %d\n", drm->hdmi_device->class);
415 pci_dev_put(drm->hdmi_device);
416 drm->hdmi_device = NULL;
417 return;
418 }
419#endif
420}
421
422static int
423nouveau_drm_load(struct drm_device *dev, unsigned long flags)
424{
425 struct nouveau_drm *drm;
426 int ret;
427
428 ret = nouveau_cli_create(dev, "DRM", sizeof(*drm), (void **)&drm);
429 if (ret)
430 return ret;
431
432 dev->dev_private = drm;
433 drm->dev = dev;
434 nvxx_client(&drm->client.base)->debug =
435 nvkm_dbgopt(nouveau_debug, "DRM");
436
437 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&drm->clients);
438 spin_lock_init(&drm->tile.lock);
439
440 nouveau_get_hdmi_dev(drm);
441
442 ret = nvif_device_init(&drm->client.base.object, 0, NV_DEVICE,
443 &(struct nv_device_v0) {
444 .device = ~0,
445 }, sizeof(struct nv_device_v0),
446 &drm->device);
447 if (ret)
448 goto fail_device;
449
450 dev->irq_enabled = true;
451
452 /* workaround an odd issue on nvc1 by disabling the device's
453 * nosnoop capability. hopefully won't cause issues until a
454 * better fix is found - assuming there is one...
455 */
456 if (drm->device.info.chipset == 0xc1)
457 nvif_mask(&drm->device.object, 0x00088080, 0x00000800, 0x00000000);
458
459 nouveau_vga_init(drm);
460
461 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_TESLA) {
462 ret = nvkm_vm_new(nvxx_device(&drm->device), 0, (1ULL << 40),
463 0x1000, NULL, &drm->client.vm);
464 if (ret)
465 goto fail_device;
466
467 nvxx_client(&drm->client.base)->vm = drm->client.vm;
468 }
469
470#ifdef __NetBSD__
471 {
472 /* XXX Kludge to make register subregion mapping work. */
473 struct nvkm_client *client = nvxx_client(&drm->client.base);
474 struct nvkm_device *device = nvxx_device(&drm->device);
475 client->mmiot = device->mmiot;
476 client->mmioh = device->mmioh;
477 client->mmioaddr = device->mmioaddr;
478 client->mmiosz = device->mmiosz;
479 }
480#endif
481
482 ret = nouveau_ttm_init(drm);
483 if (ret)
484 goto fail_ttm;
485
486 ret = nouveau_bios_init(dev);
487 if (ret)
488 goto fail_bios;
489
490 ret = nouveau_display_create(dev);
491 if (ret)
492 goto fail_dispctor;
493
494 if (dev->mode_config.num_crtc) {
495 ret = nouveau_display_init(dev);
496 if (ret)
497 goto fail_dispinit;
498 }
499
500 nouveau_sysfs_init(dev);
501 nouveau_hwmon_init(dev);
502 nouveau_accel_init(drm);
503 nouveau_fbcon_init(dev);
504
505 if (nouveau_runtime_pm != 0) {
506 pm_runtime_use_autosuspend(dev->dev);
507 pm_runtime_set_autosuspend_delay(dev->dev, 5000);
508 pm_runtime_set_active(dev->dev);
509 pm_runtime_allow(dev->dev);
510 pm_runtime_mark_last_busy(dev->dev);
511 pm_runtime_put(dev->dev);
512 }
513 return 0;
514
515fail_dispinit:
516 nouveau_display_destroy(dev);
517fail_dispctor:
518 nouveau_bios_takedown(dev);
519fail_bios:
520 nouveau_ttm_fini(drm);
521fail_ttm:
522 nouveau_vga_fini(drm);
523fail_device:
524 nvif_device_fini(&drm->device);
525 nouveau_cli_destroy(&drm->client);
526 return ret;
527}
528
529static int
530nouveau_drm_unload(struct drm_device *dev)
531{
532 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
533
534 pm_runtime_get_sync(dev->dev);
535 nouveau_fbcon_fini(dev);
536 nouveau_accel_fini(drm);
537 nouveau_hwmon_fini(dev);
538 nouveau_sysfs_fini(dev);
539
540 if (dev->mode_config.num_crtc)
541 nouveau_display_fini(dev);
542 nouveau_display_destroy(dev);
543
544 nouveau_bios_takedown(dev);
545
546 nouveau_ttm_fini(drm);
547 nouveau_vga_fini(drm);
548
549 nvif_device_fini(&drm->device);
550#ifndef __NetBSD__ /* XXX nouveau hdmi */
551 if (drm->hdmi_device)
552 pci_dev_put(drm->hdmi_device);
553#endif
554 nouveau_cli_destroy(&drm->client);
555 return 0;
556}

559void
560nouveau_drm_device_remove(struct drm_device *dev)
561{
562 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
563 struct nvkm_client *client;
564 struct nvkm_device *device;
565
566 dev->irq_enabled = false;
567 client = nvxx_client(&drm->client.base);
568 device = nvkm_device_find(client->device);
569 drm_put_dev(dev);
570
571 nvkm_device_del(&device);
572}

579 nouveau_drm_device_remove(dev);
580}

583static int
584nouveau_do_suspend(struct drm_device *dev, bool runtime)
585{
586 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
587 struct nouveau_cli *cli;
588 int ret;
589
590 if (dev->mode_config.num_crtc) {
591 NV_INFO(drm, "suspending console...\n");
592 nouveau_fbcon_set_suspend(dev, 1);
593 NV_INFO(drm, "suspending display...\n");
594 ret = nouveau_display_suspend(dev, runtime);
595 if (ret)
596 return ret;
597 }
598
599 NV_INFO(drm, "evicting buffers...\n");
600 ttm_bo_evict_mm(&drm->ttm.bdev, TTM_PL_VRAM);
601
602 NV_INFO(drm, "waiting for kernel channels to go idle...\n");
603 if (drm->cechan) {
604 ret = nouveau_channel_idle(drm->cechan);
605 if (ret)
606 goto fail_display;
607 }
608
609 if (drm->channel) {
610 ret = nouveau_channel_idle(drm->channel);
611 if (ret)
612 goto fail_display;
613 }
614
615 NV_INFO(drm, "suspending client object trees...\n");
616 if (drm->fence && nouveau_fence(drm)->suspend) {
617 if (!nouveau_fence(drm)->suspend(drm)) {
618 ret = -ENOMEM;
619 goto fail_display;
620 }
621 }
622
623 list_for_each_entry(cli, &drm->clients, head) {
624 ret = nvif_client_suspend(&cli->base);
625 if (ret)
626 goto fail_client;
627 }
628
629 NV_INFO(drm, "suspending kernel object tree...\n");
630 ret = nvif_client_suspend(&drm->client.base);
631 if (ret)
632 goto fail_client;
633
634 return 0;
635
636fail_client:
637 list_for_each_entry_continue_reverse(cli, &drm->clients, head) {
638 nvif_client_resume(&cli->base);
639 }
640
641 if (drm->fence && nouveau_fence(drm)->resume)
642 nouveau_fence(drm)->resume(drm);
643
644fail_display:
645 if (dev->mode_config.num_crtc) {
646 NV_INFO(drm, "resuming display...\n");
647 nouveau_display_resume(dev, runtime);
648 }
649 return ret;
650}
651
652static int
653nouveau_do_resume(struct drm_device *dev, bool runtime)
654{
655 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
656 struct nouveau_cli *cli;
657
658 NV_INFO(drm, "resuming kernel object tree...\n");
659 nvif_client_resume(&drm->client.base);
660
661 NV_INFO(drm, "resuming client object trees...\n");
662 if (drm->fence && nouveau_fence(drm)->resume)
663 nouveau_fence(drm)->resume(drm);
664
665 list_for_each_entry(cli, &drm->clients, head) {
666 nvif_client_resume(&cli->base);
667 }
668
669 nouveau_run_vbios_init(dev);
670
671 if (dev->mode_config.num_crtc) {
672 NV_INFO(drm, "resuming display...\n");
673 nouveau_display_resume(dev, runtime);
674 NV_INFO(drm, "resuming console...\n");
675 nouveau_fbcon_set_suspend(dev, 0);
676 }
677
678 return 0;
679}
680
681int
682#ifdef __NetBSD__
683nouveau_pmops_suspend(struct drm_device *drm_dev)
684#else
685nouveau_pmops_suspend(struct device *dev)
686#endif
687{
688#ifndef __NetBSD__
689 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
690 struct drm_device *drm_dev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
691#endif
692 int ret;
693
694 if (drm_dev->switch_power_state == DRM_SWITCH_POWER_OFF ||
695 drm_dev->switch_power_state == DRM_SWITCH_POWER_DYNAMIC_OFF)
696 return 0;
697
698 ret = nouveau_do_suspend(drm_dev, false);
699 if (ret)
700 return ret;
701
702#ifndef __NetBSD__ /* pmf handles this for us. */
703 pci_save_state(pdev);
704 pci_disable_device(pdev);
705 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D3hot);
706#endif
707 udelay(200);
708 return 0;
709}
710
711int
712#ifdef __NetBSD__
713nouveau_pmops_resume(struct drm_device *drm_dev)
714#else
715nouveau_pmops_resume(struct device *dev)
716#endif
717{
718#ifndef __NetBSD__
719 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
720 struct drm_device *drm_dev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
721 int ret;
722#endif
723
724 if (drm_dev->switch_power_state == DRM_SWITCH_POWER_OFF ||
725 drm_dev->switch_power_state == DRM_SWITCH_POWER_DYNAMIC_OFF)
726 return 0;
727
728#ifndef __NetBSD__ /* pmf handles this for us */
729 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D0);
730 pci_restore_state(pdev);
731 ret = pci_enable_device(pdev);
732 if (ret)
733 return ret;
734 pci_set_master(pdev);
735#endif
736
737 return nouveau_do_resume(drm_dev, false);
738}
739
740#ifndef __NetBSD__ /* XXX nouveau pm */
741static int
742nouveau_pmops_freeze(struct device *dev)
743{
744 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
745 struct drm_device *drm_dev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
746 return nouveau_do_suspend(drm_dev, false);
747}

754 return nouveau_do_resume(drm_dev, false);

756
757static int
758nouveau_pmops_runtime_suspend(struct device *dev)
759{
760 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
761 struct drm_device *drm_dev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
762 int ret;
763
764 if (nouveau_runtime_pm == 0) {
765 pm_runtime_forbid(dev);
766 return -EBUSY;
767 }
768
769 /* are we optimus enabled? */
770 if (nouveau_runtime_pm == -1 && !nouveau_is_optimus() && !nouveau_is_v1_dsm()) {
771 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("failing to power off - not optimus\n");
772 pm_runtime_forbid(dev);
773 return -EBUSY;
774 }
775
776 drm_kms_helper_poll_disable(drm_dev);
777 vga_switcheroo_set_dynamic_switch(pdev, VGA_SWITCHEROO_OFF);
778 nouveau_switcheroo_optimus_dsm();
779 ret = nouveau_do_suspend(drm_dev, true);
780 pci_save_state(pdev);
781 pci_disable_device(pdev);
782 pci_ignore_hotplug(pdev);
783 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D3cold);
784 drm_dev->switch_power_state = DRM_SWITCH_POWER_DYNAMIC_OFF;
785 return ret;
786}
787
788static int
789nouveau_pmops_runtime_resume(struct device *dev)
790{
791 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
792 struct drm_device *drm_dev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
793 struct nvif_device *device = &nouveau_drm(drm_dev)->device;
794 int ret;
795
796 if (nouveau_runtime_pm == 0)
797 return -EINVAL;
798
799 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D0);
800 pci_restore_state(pdev);
801 ret = pci_enable_device(pdev);
802 if (ret)
803 return ret;
804 pci_set_master(pdev);
805
806 ret = nouveau_do_resume(drm_dev, true);
807
808 if (!drm_dev->mode_config.poll_enabled)
809 drm_kms_helper_poll_enable(drm_dev);
810
811 /* do magic */
812 nvif_mask(&device->object, 0x088488, (1 << 25), (1 << 25));
813 vga_switcheroo_set_dynamic_switch(pdev, VGA_SWITCHEROO_ON);
814 drm_dev->switch_power_state = DRM_SWITCH_POWER_ON;
815 return ret;
816}
817
818static int
819nouveau_pmops_runtime_idle(struct device *dev)
820{
821 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
822 struct drm_device *drm_dev = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
823 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(drm_dev);
824 struct drm_crtc *crtc;
825
826 if (nouveau_runtime_pm == 0) {
827 pm_runtime_forbid(dev);
828 return -EBUSY;
829 }
830
831 /* are we optimus enabled? */
832 if (nouveau_runtime_pm == -1 && !nouveau_is_optimus() && !nouveau_is_v1_dsm()) {
833 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("failing to power off - not optimus\n");
834 pm_runtime_forbid(dev);
835 return -EBUSY;
836 }
837
838 /* if we have a hdmi audio device - make sure it has a driver loaded */
839 if (drm->hdmi_device) {
840 if (!drm->hdmi_device->driver) {
841 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("failing to power off - no HDMI audio driver loaded\n");
842 pm_runtime_mark_last_busy(dev);
843 return -EBUSY;
844 }
845 }
846
847 list_for_each_entry(crtc, &drm->dev->mode_config.crtc_list, head) {
848 if (crtc->enabled) {
849 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("failing to power off - crtc active\n");
850 return -EBUSY;
851 }
852 }
853 pm_runtime_mark_last_busy(dev);
854 pm_runtime_autosuspend(dev);
855 /* we don't want the main rpm_idle to call suspend - we want to autosuspend */
856 return 1;
857}
858#endif /* XXX nouveau pm */
859
860static int
861nouveau_drm_open(struct drm_device *dev, struct drm_file *fpriv)
862{
863 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
864 struct nouveau_cli *cli;
865#ifdef __NetBSD__
866 const char name[] = "user";
867#else
868 char name[32], tmpname[TASK_COMM_LEN];
869#endif
870 int ret;
871
872 /* need to bring up power immediately if opening device */
873 ret = pm_runtime_get_sync(dev->dev);
874 if (ret < 0 && ret != -EACCES)
875 return ret;
876
877#ifndef __NetBSD__
878 get_task_comm(tmpname, current);
879 snprintf(name, sizeof(name), "%s[%d]", tmpname, pid_nr(fpriv->pid));
880#endif
881
882 ret = nouveau_cli_create(dev, name, sizeof(*cli), (void **)&cli);
883
884 if (ret)
885 goto out_suspend;
886
887 cli->base.super = false;
888
889 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_TESLA) {
890 ret = nvkm_vm_new(nvxx_device(&drm->device), 0, (1ULL << 40),
891 0x1000, NULL, &cli->vm);
892 if (ret) {
893 nouveau_cli_destroy(cli);
894 goto out_suspend;
895 }
896
897 nvxx_client(&cli->base)->vm = cli->vm;
898 }
899
900 fpriv->driver_priv = cli;
901
902 mutex_lock(&drm->client.mutex);
903 list_add(&cli->head, &drm->clients);
904 mutex_unlock(&drm->client.mutex);
905
906out_suspend:
907 pm_runtime_mark_last_busy(dev->dev);
908 pm_runtime_put_autosuspend(dev->dev);
909
910 return ret;
911}
912
913static void
914nouveau_drm_preclose(struct drm_device *dev, struct drm_file *fpriv)
915{
916 struct nouveau_cli *cli = nouveau_cli(fpriv);
917 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
918
919 pm_runtime_get_sync(dev->dev);
920
921 mutex_lock(&cli->mutex);
922 if (cli->abi16)
923 nouveau_abi16_fini(cli->abi16);
924 mutex_unlock(&cli->mutex);
925
926 mutex_lock(&drm->client.mutex);
927 list_del(&cli->head);
928 mutex_unlock(&drm->client.mutex);
929
930}
931
932static void
933nouveau_drm_postclose(struct drm_device *dev, struct drm_file *fpriv)
934{
935 struct nouveau_cli *cli = nouveau_cli(fpriv);
936 nouveau_cli_destroy(cli);
937 pm_runtime_mark_last_busy(dev->dev);
938 pm_runtime_put_autosuspend(dev->dev);
939}

957#ifdef __NetBSD__
958#include <sys/file.h>
959#include <sys/ioccom.h>
960static int /* XXX expose to ioc32 */
961nouveau_ioctl_override(struct file *fp, unsigned long cmd, void *data)
962{
963 struct drm_file *file = fp->f_data;
964 struct drm_device *dev = file->minor->dev;
965 int ret;
966
967 ret = pm_runtime_get_sync(dev->dev);
968 if (ret < 0 && ret != -EACCES)
969 /* XXX errno Linux->NetBSD */
970 return -ret;
971
972 switch (DRM_IOCTL_NR(cmd) - DRM_COMMAND_BASE) {
973 case DRM_NOUVEAU_NVIF:
974 /* XXX errno Linux->NetBSD */
975 ret = -usif_ioctl(file, data, IOCPARM_LEN(cmd));
976 break;
977 default:
978 ret = drm_ioctl(fp, cmd, data);
979 break;
980 }
981
982 pm_runtime_mark_last_busy(dev->dev);
983 pm_runtime_put_autosuspend(dev->dev);
984 return ret;
985}
986#else
987long
988nouveau_drm_ioctl(struct file *file, unsigned int cmd, unsigned long arg)
989{
990 struct drm_file *filp = file->private_data;
991 struct drm_device *dev = filp->minor->dev;
992 long ret;
993
994 ret = pm_runtime_get_sync(dev->dev);
995 if (ret < 0 && ret != -EACCES)
996 return ret;
997
998 switch (_IOC_NR(cmd) - DRM_COMMAND_BASE) {
999 case DRM_NOUVEAU_NVIF:
1000 ret = usif_ioctl(filp, (void __user *)arg, _IOC_SIZE(cmd));
1001 break;
1002 default:
1003 ret = drm_ioctl(file, cmd, arg);
1004 break;
1005 }
1006
1007 pm_runtime_mark_last_busy(dev->dev);
1008 pm_runtime_put_autosuspend(dev->dev);
1009 return ret;
1010}
1011#endif

1157struct drm_device *
1158nouveau_platform_device_create(const struct nvkm_device_tegra_func *func,
1159 struct platform_device *pdev,
1160 struct nvkm_device **pdevice)
1161{
1162 struct drm_device *drm;
1163 int err;
1164
1165 err = nvkm_device_tegra_new(func, pdev, nouveau_config, nouveau_debug,
1166 true, true, ~0ULL, pdevice);
1167 if (err)
1168 goto err_free;
1169
1170 drm = drm_dev_alloc(&driver_platform, &pdev->dev);
1171 if (!drm) {
1172 err = -ENOMEM;
1173 goto err_free;
1174 }
1175
1176 err = drm_dev_set_unique(drm, "%s", dev_name(&pdev->dev));
1177 if (err < 0)
1178 goto err_free;
1179
1180 drm->platformdev = pdev;
1181 platform_set_drvdata(pdev, drm);
1182
1183 return drm;
1184
1185err_free:
1186 nvkm_device_del(pdevice);
1187
1188 return ERR_PTR(err);
1189}

1191static int __init
1192nouveau_drm_init(void)
1193{
1194 driver_pci = driver_stub;
1195 driver_pci.set_busid = drm_pci_set_busid;
1196 driver_platform = driver_stub;
1197 driver_platform.set_busid = drm_platform_set_busid;
1198
1199 nouveau_display_options();
1200
1201 if (nouveau_modeset == -1) {
1202#ifdef CONFIG_VGA_CONSOLE
1203 if (vgacon_text_force())
1204 nouveau_modeset = 0;
1205#endif
1206 }
1207
1208 if (!nouveau_modeset)
1209 return 0;
1210
1211#ifdef CONFIG_NOUVEAU_PLATFORM_DRIVER
1212 platform_driver_register(&nouveau_platform_driver);
1213#endif
1214
1215 nouveau_register_dsm_handler();
1216 return drm_pci_init(&driver_pci, &nouveau_drm_pci_driver);
1217}

1219static void __exit
1220nouveau_drm_exit(void)
1221{
1222 if (!nouveau_modeset)
1223 return;
1224
1225 drm_pci_exit(&driver_pci, &nouveau_drm_pci_driver);
1226 nouveau_unregister_dsm_handler();
1227
1228#ifdef CONFIG_NOUVEAU_PLATFORM_DRIVER
1229 platform_driver_unregister(&nouveau_platform_driver);
1230#endif
1231}
1232#endif
